    <element xsi:type="archimate:Assessment" name="Time to Money" id="id-852f742fabeb406cbed2970124ac4ba4">
      <documentation>Onboarding = time to money – need synergy and alignment across business units and products</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Assessment" name="Market Share" id="id-86952a423d9c4c93a38917d6d242f250"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Assessment" name="Profit Before Tax (PBT)" id="id-b1325ef139a643e385533c44d513feb8"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Assessment" name="Speed (processing and execution)" id="id-f0ab00d39ab847048c52030794096554"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Automate for straight-through-processing (STP) and risk mitigation" id="id-0b632752524b4946bcdfd9d0373037f0"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Treasury Management System / Dashboard – just getting visibility of the client’s data re: their cash – into the future = forecasting" id="id-193a0344b028435d82a7ad44ca4096e4">
      <documentation>Client treasury is not as advanced as would be expected – they have to do a lot of fancy excel to get insights and reliant on bank data across the industry (multi-jurisdiction and multi-bank)&#xD;
Sponsor segment doesn’t have Treasurers, they have 3rd parties / finance or fund managers &#xD;
So many accounts (risky and expensive) and treasurers want a way to automate and improve reconciliations, not just domestic, more international (MNCs) – there is definitely value to be unlocked = virtual accounts? (Note: recons are why payment / transaction data has huge focus – look at real time updates and transaction reference matching to enable receivables? Account enabler must look at transaction data classification and referencing frameworks to enable better reconciliations across the board.) </documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Mobile Wallet integration, first foundations, then collection rails" id="id-6f9b2f535aff4e3e821abf6fd7f2ec82"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Small credit mandate – corporate credit model is too expensive and takes too long for companies that are cash flush, only require an overdraft, and don’t require such rigour, need a more appropriate credit scoring model for quick decision making" id="id-80a8b4fff87c4e3e8f74f07fbf5f3841"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Onboarding &amp; Servicing: clients get fed-up with the process and we lose that revenue/business (existing and new clients)" id="id-82a9b58efc9647ad9f681cce4d22fa55">
      <documentation>Onboarding &amp; Servicing: clients get fed-up with the process and we lose that revenue/business (existing and new clients)</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="First mover advantage on Request to Pay will gain the market in the next 3 to 5 years" id="id-886beab3f81d4f82bbbb18428650032f"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Profitability and Growth" id="id-abb40f753b7647fdb2d4c1ee7863dd51"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Clients operate across Africa, we can see their revenue, but not their operations – need to look at ways of doing this market research for the broader Africa growth strategy and adjacent opportunities" id="id-b2eb47d6fe3f4064826b58c6c915f04a"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Sales: It takes 6 sales analysts 2 weeks to prepare packs for sales conversations " id="id-c27c6500f98345b7bcbd5e759bfc50d1"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Foundational capability problems preventing execution on sales strategies" id="id-c340759417af4978b6807c00d4e8f800"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Driver" name="Client have been asking for the same things for (at least 8) years" id="id-c3d5a34635bc4b5f92117acaa72c5eb0"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Goal" name="Protect and Grow SA market share" id="id-941ab67d7a4544e49c7263f1e674f14f"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Goal" name="Request to Pay - @Till and eCommerce, via APIs and H2H" id="id-a39fe053b67b4250b2d59f103453b406"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Goal" name="Cross-selling: clients don’t use our full suite of services so there are obvious cross-selling opportunities for the full TTS portfolios" id="id-a577e5ac8c3945f2b2d115f62482a913"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Goal" name="Seamless channel, sales and service enablement of new products and features – cannot sell what a client cannot ACCESS" id="id-b146d3643b98497bab1ee1f6b1e12b99"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Goal" name="Transact Product Management: Account Services, Card, Fleet, Cash, EFT, Merchant Services, RAS and FX Payments - on behalf of TTS ie product development, profitability" id="id-dba4da57beb64952bc2fc9e6357eb451"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Goal" name="Offer competitive AVS" id="id-e12a76a5bd3b4538997bfafb0e1ff07e"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Goal" name="Real time payments with failover / backup / client and bank BCP (like alternative rails) as these are currently routed to other banks (corporate and commercial requirement)" id="id-edd9d3eaa9914da4b4892587c3382f5b"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Outcome" name="Less time (how much?) required to prepare portfolio reviews" id="id-529bc64bb34b49d197fb57ea9acc631f">
      <documentation>Too many clients and a lot of work to consolidate, can’t get through the conversations fast enough</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Outcome" name="Trigger model should increase contribution by R3-12mil" id="id-a6b3c6d25a4e40ffa4822992eba082ac"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Outcome" name="Retain current TTS client base" id="id-a91ac4c6a2ce410bb51f07c58212391f"/>
