            <sourceConnection xsi:type="archimate:Connection" id="id-a320d9b3ce144f3e84b6cfa1d6d68675" source="id-17d8e3b701404857a349d95807cab417" target="id-73dcf3b71bd34661a4b1b8dd18d7978f" archimateRelationship="id-7945a9adab5f4b3d9965b794a88adf88"/>
          </child>
        </child>
        <documentation>Key offerings being pursued in Transact now, but require enablement: &#xD;
1. Account Verification Services – exploring Nutron partnership for profile verification services, which incorporates credit and profile and proof of life and residence&#xD;
2. Payroll – partnering with PaySpace for earned wage access to credit&#xD;
Rewards as behavioural incentives&#xD;
3. All of these are now being finalised with Legal, but next step is to Operationalise &#xD;
4. We need a framework of putting standard legal agreements in place with partners.&#xD;
&#xD;
Key problems and opportunities:  &#xD;
1. Presence in Marketplaces, esp. nav>> requires Catalogue – enabled with AI to answer questions on the solutions catalogue&#xD;
2. There is a resistance to self-service, so staff-assisted first with sales support (for onboarding, then servicing and transacting)&#xD;
3. Too many sales areas and then balls get dropped thinking someone else has got it, for example: Merchant Services – sales teams in Coverage (Client Groups), TxP (Tamara) and MS Sales teams&#xD;
</documentation>
      </element>
    </folder>
