            <child xsi:type="archimate:Note" id="id-8711dc3cfe25496db13548dc80f2ccc3" textAlignment="1">
              <bounds x="1919" y="407" width="180" height="74"/>
              <content>30 day rule  - client buys currency for 30 days - but has to be used / can't hold the position&#xD;
export proceeds can keep funds indefinitely - can put the funds on deposit. Clients responsibility to make sure that the funds are permissible.&#xD;
</content>
            </child>
            <child xsi:type="archimate:Note" id="id-41f88d30fa184b70abeeb80a441fd58c" textAlignment="1">
              <bounds x="2098" y="432" width="218" height="74"/>
              <content>if we are pushing funds offshore - then we have to report&#xD;
&#xD;
currency deposits - are they deemed offshore / onshore? &#xD;
&#xD;
FCA accounts are deemed offshore - gets reported when we put the money into the account. </content>
            </child>
