              <child xsi:type="archimate:Note" id="id-fcd68272d0ba4d6984feb19ef10b268d" textAlignment="1">
                <bounds x="2112" y="179" width="385" height="121"/>
                <content>1. Debit Finxact Term Deposit (same counterparty), Credit CFC in our books (Hogan) (Credit Transfer Instruction)&#xD;
2. Send an outward SWIFT for funds (pacs.008 serial / cover)&#xD;
	a. outward SWIFT to overseas bank&#xD;
	b. outward SWIFT to local bank&#xD;
&#xD;
Correspondent Banking account/ Mirror Nostro in our books. </content>
              </child>
              <child xsi:type="archimate:Note" id="id-555630c1c4c547ac8623918923db9d75" textAlignment="1">
                <bounds x="2520" y="73" width="721" height="226"/>
                <content>TTS will have a cash settlement accounts for each currency- like IBD and Markets. &#xD;
TTS USD - Finxact &#xD;
TTS GBP - Finxact&#xD;
TTS EUR - Finxact&#xD;
TTS ZAR - Finxact? &#xD;
Reconciled daily to the General Ledger&#xD;
&#xD;
Set up bank accounts to enable the TTS business on Finxact. &#xD;
Hogan multi-currency accounts - belong to TTS. (Back-end funding - Cornelia to provide accounting numbers - ask someone from Hogan to give us the front-end business account numbers - ask FXPH). &#xD;
&#xD;
Ask Ivan and Amit where we account for Treasury's ledger - can we create a Treasury book on Finxact. Set up a separate account for Treasury on the FICS ledger. Open Treasury book / centre on Finxact. - Will still aggregate across source systems. Will have to combine this with the Murex position? Will they be willing to aggregate?  </content>
              </child>
