                <bounds x="1884" y="108" width="385" height="148"/>
                <content>1. Debit CFC in our books (Hogan), Credit Finxact Term Deposit (same counterparty) (Credit Transfer Instruction)&#xD;
2. Await an inward SWIFT for funds (Receipt)&#xD;
	a. inward SWIFT from overseas bank&#xD;
	b. inward SWIFT from local bank&#xD;
	Correspondent Banking account/ Mirror Nostro in our books. &#xD;
3. Debit Call/Notice account (Chameleon), Credit Finxact?&#xD;
4. Debit Finxact Term Deposit that is maturing (for rollovers)</content>
              </child>
              <child xsi:type="archimate:Note" id="id-5ab3cf214bcb41288b44360ff2fdf160" textAlignment="1">
                <bounds x="2280" y="101" width="769" height="154"/>
                <content>TTS will have a cash settlement accounts for each currency- like IBD and Markets.  > TTS USD/GBP/EUR - Finxact, but TTS ZAR - Finxact? Reconciled daily to the General Ledger&#xD;
&#xD;
Set up bank accounts to enable the TTS business on Finxact. &#xD;
Hogan multi-currency accounts - belong to TTS. (Back-end funding - Cornelia to provide accounting numbers - ask someone from Hogan to give us the front-end business account numbers - ask FXPH). &#xD;
&#xD;
Ask Ivan and Amit where we account for Treasury's ledger - can we create a Treasury book on Finxact. Set up a separate account for Treasury on the FICS ledger. Open Treasury book / centre on Finxact. - Will still aggregate across source systems. Will have to combine this with the Murex position? Will they be willing to aggregate?  </content>
              </child>
