          <child xsi:type="archimate:Note" id="id-d32360934d46464792fddf7b704abfeb" textAlignment="1" fillColor="#e7e6e6">
            <bounds x="528" y="252" width="217" height="73"/>
            <content>The JSE acts as a Payment System Operator as they determine the settlement bank for each broker and route the instructions accordingly.</content>
          </child>
          <child xsi:type="archimate:Note" id="id-1569006e624442f1bd3722a09fb26262" fontColor="#ff0000" textAlignment="1">
            <bounds x="1296" y="324" width="181" height="85"/>
            <content>Is the #10 instruction is a duplicate of #12 and only for controlled clients as it is a debit to the broker's account anyway and not a JSE Trust account?</content>
          </child>
        </child>
